# HippoTail — Literature Map

Maintained by: LitBoss  
Last updated: 2026-03-07
This document summarizes the key literature relevant to hippocampal tail connectivity.

The goal is to identify:

• established knowledge  
• unresolved questions  
• contradictions in the field  
• opportunities for new hypotheses  

---

# Key Papers

### CCEP Connectivity Mapping

Lyu et al. Nature Neuroscience 2025

Contribution  
Introduced F1 statistic (R) for cortico-cortico evoked potential connectivity.

Relevance  
Primary connectivity metric used in HippoTail analysis.

---

### Hippocampal Longitudinal Axis

Key insight  
Anterior and posterior hippocampus have distinct connectivity patterns.

Evidence  
fMRI and tractography studies.

Gap  
Causal connectivity using CCEP has not been tested.

---

### Mesial Temporal Sclerosis

Observation  
Sclerosis may extend into hippocampal tail.

Implication  
Posterior hippocampus may participate in seizure networks.

---

# Literature Gaps

Current gaps in knowledge:

1. Effective connectivity of hippocampal tail is poorly characterized.
2. Directional connectivity between tail and thalamus is unclear.
3. Contralateral hippocampal tail connectivity has not been systematically mapped.

